0 \\leq a^{2} \\cos ^{2} x-2 a b \\sin x \\cos x+b^{2} \\sin ^{2} x \\\\
(a \\cos x-b \\sin x)^{2} \\geq 0
\\end{gathered}$$

The last inequality is true for any $a, b$ and $x$. 
Therefore the initial inequality $a \\sin x+b \\cos x \\leq \\sqrt{a^{2}+b^{2}}$ is true as well. 
